. This book offers the first comprehensive analysis of international efforts to promote democracy during the post–World War II period, with an emphasis on developments since 1989. The authors assess the efforts of major industrialized democracies, multilateral actors, and NGOs. They find that the success of these endeavors is constrained by several realities, ranging from the often significant gap between the rhetoric and the reality of actual policies, to the dilemma that occurs when the goal of democracy clashes with other foreign policy interests.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aDemocratization. 0aDémocratisation. 0aDéveloppement politique. 0aPolitical development. 0aPolitique mondialex1989-. 0aWorld politicsx1989-. 0aWorld politicsy1989-. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh1 aAkaha, Tsuneo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHermann, Margaret G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHibou, Béatrice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHook, Steven W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Juliet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJoyner, Christopher C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKegley, Charles W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaakso, Liisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOlsen, Gorm Rye, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRüland, Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchraeder, Peter J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchraeder, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary